AnnieMurphyPaul_2011G 1 AnnieMurphyPaul_2011G 122.2 139.78 <o,f0,female> and one of the most fascinating insights i took from this work is that we 're all learning about the world even before we enter it when we hold our babies for the first time we might imagine that they 're clean slates unmarked by life
AnnieMurphyPaul_2011G 1 AnnieMurphyPaul_2011G 139.78 155.77 <o,f0,female> when in fact they 've already been shaped by us and by the particular world we live in today i want to share with you some of the amazing things that scientists are discovering about what fetuses learn while they 're still in their mothers bellies
